product_name: FENTY BEAUTY by RihannaGrip Trip Mattifying + Blurring Primer
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeA gripping primer with mattifying + blurring skincare benefits that delivers a smooth, filtered finish that makes your makeup last up to 12 hours + resists sweat & humidity. Maple Sap Extract locks in makeup + Chia Seed Extract mattifies. This silicone-free primer creates the perfect canvas.
details: DetailsBenefitsInstantly mattifies skin for a blurred + filtered finishNon-drying + reduces shineResists sweat + humidityNo flashbackKey IngredientsMaple Sap Extract extends makeup wear for up to 12 hoursChia Seed Extract to mattify and control shineItem 2646008How To UseFor the ultimate smooth and blurred effect, use fingers to press primer into the skin - a little goes a long way. how_to_use: For the ultimate smooth and blurred effect, use fingers to press primer into the skin - a little goes a long way. Start at the center of the face and work your way out.

reviews.headline: For the oily girls
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I'm an oily girlie and I think I just found my favorite primer. This was a smooth matte primer that hid my pores and kept me from glistening. I applied 2 layers and was set. I usually am sensitive to products but had no issue here. Mwahhh

reviews.headline: Mattifying and Longwearing
reviews.comments: I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest review! Upon first look I think the swirl design inside is so cool, pretty, and very eye catching. This product has chia seed extract which is meant to help mattify and control surface oil and maple sap extract to help it grip the skin and extend the wear of your makeup which it 100% does. It feels lightweight and breathable on the skin and is the perfect primer to use before makeup application if you have oily skin and large pores. I don't think it completely erased every pore on my face so the blur to me was minimal. I will continue to reach for this primer! I am very impressed with it.

reviews.headline: Smooth makeup application

You get a smooth finish and some mattifying but don't get it confused with oil reducing since after 8hrs, shine came through.  Initial use is great just use a setting spray with oil control for even better results.

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] As someone who has struggled with oily skin and makeup that tends to slip and slide throughout the day, I was excited to try Fenty Beauty's Grip Trip Mattifying + Blurring Primer. After using it for a few weeks, I can confidently say that this primer has become a staple in my makeup routine.

First and foremost, the primer delivers on its promise of all-day shine control. I have combination skin, and my T-zone can get quite oily by midday. However, when using the Grip Trip primer, I noticed a significant reduction in shine and oil production. My makeup stayed matte and fresh-looking for hours longer than it would with other primers I've tried.

The blurring effect of the primer is another standout feature. It smooths out my pores and fine lines, creating a flawless canvas for foundation application. This, combined with the mattifying properties, ensures that my makeup looks smooth and even all day long.

I was also impressed with the primer's ability to resist sweat and humidity. I live in a hot and humid climate, and many primers have failed to keep my makeup intact during the summer months. However, the Grip Trip primer held up remarkably well, even in the most challenging conditions.

One concern I had was that the primer might cause flashback in photos, but I was pleased to find that it didn't. The formula is completely translucent and doesn't leave a white cast on my skin, making it perfect for use in any lighting situation.

Another benefit of the Grip Trip primer is that it doesn't pill under foundation. Some primers can cause my foundation to bunch up or become uneven, but this primer allows my foundation to glide on smoothly and seamlessly.

Lastly, the primer extends my makeup wear by up to 12 hours. This is a significant improvement over other primers I've used, which often leave my makeup looking patchy or faded by the end of the day.

In conclusion, Fenty Beauty's Grip Trip Mattifying + Blurring Primer is a game-changer for those with oily or combination skin. It provides all-day shine control, a blurring effect, resistance to sweat and humidity, no flashback, and extended makeup wear. I highly recommend this primer to anyone looking for a high-performing, long-lasting base for their makeup routine.
faceoff_positive.headline: Wow

faceoff_negative.comments:
As someone with very oily skin, a high-quality primer is essential in my makeup routine, so I was excited to try the Fenty Beauty Mattifying & Blurring Face Primer. My experience was a mix of highs and lows.
Packaging: I wasn't a fan of the two-tone bottle with the pink swirl‚Äîit felt busy compared to my preference for clean, minimal designs. That said, it arrived securely with padding, preventing spills.
Scent: Almost fragrance-free, which is perfect for sensitive skin. It's subtle, calming, and non-irritating.
Texture & Application: Smooth, creamy, and lightweight, it glides easily without tugging or pilling. It layers well under liquid foundation and powder, giving an instant blurring effect that minimizes pores and fine lines naturally.
Effectiveness: The primer initially delivers a soft-matte finish with zero flashback, helping foundation sit evenly. I added two pictures from different occasions to show the finish. However, after about four hours, my T-zone became shiny, requiring translucent powder touch-ups. While it works short-term, it lacks the long-lasting oil control I expected.
Price & Value: Fair for a high-end, accessible brand, but performance on very oily skin may not justify the cost if all-day mattification is needed.
Overall Quality: Pros: smooth texture, minimal scent, blurring effect, skin-friendly, zero flashback. Cons: packaging design (personal taste), limited oil-control longevity.
I'd score this 5/10 for effectiveness. It's great for a lightweight, skin-friendly base with a soft-matte finish, but for truly oily skin, it may fall short compared to other primers.
faceoff_negative.headline: A beautifully blurring primer with zero flashback
